article.headline: Lafayette 76, Mount St. Mary's, Md. 72
article.story: EMMITSBURG, Md. (AP) -- Andrew Brown scored a game-high 32 points, and Lafayette defeated Mount St. Mary's, Md., 76-72 Friday night. Michael Gruner's jumper with 13:30 remaining in the game gave Lafayette a 59-37 lead and the Leopards (8-3) held a 65-45 lead with 10:05 on the clock. The Mount (6-5) responded with a 28 to 7 run, capped by Will Holland's 3-pointer with 40 seconds remaining to cut the Lafayette lead to 73-72. On the ensuing possession, Brown sank his ninth 3-pointer of the game from the top of the key to seal the victory. Chris Vann scored a team-high 27 points to pace the Mount, who saw their six-game winning streak ended.
